== 历史谬误 ==

影片最备受争议的一幕是中情局班加西主管“鲍勃”告诉当地等待保卫大使馆许可的军方探员“休整”，从而否认他们的许可。真正的中情局主管表示没有休整命令<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/movies/former-benghazi-cia-chief-slams-13-hours-secret-soldiers-benghazi-n497506|title=Former Benghazi CIA Chief Slams '13 Hours: The Secret Soldiers of Benghazi'|first=Corky|last=Siemaszko|publisher=NBC News|accessdate=2016-01-17|archive-date=2016-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160116222017/http://www.nbcnews.com/pop-culture/movies/former-benghazi-cia-chief-slams-13-hours-secret-soldiers-benghazi-n497506|dead-url=no}}</ref>。两党共建的参议院情报委员会调查发现“没有基地主管或其它方故意拖延或干扰的证据”，支持了他的说法<ref name=Beauchamp >{{cite web|url=http://www.vox.com/2016/1/15/10774928/13-hours-benghazi-michael-bay|title=Michael Bay's 13 Hours promotes some of the worst Benghazi conspiracy theories|first=Zack|last=Beauchamp|date=2016-01-15|work=Vox|accessdate=2016-01-17|archive-date=2016-01-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117050550/http://www.vox.com/2016/1/15/10774928/13-hours-benghazi-michael-bay|dead-url=no}}</ref>。不过，《[[国家评论|国家评论]]》时事评论员{{le|大卫·F·芬奇|David F. French}}批评参议院委员会引用大量个人证词形式的“休整”命令证据，只不过选择采用相反的证词推翻影片说法<ref name="French">{{cite web |title=13 Hours: Of Course There's Evidence of a ‘Stand-Down  Order’ in Benghazi |url=http://www.nationalreview.com/corner/429855/13-hours-yes-there-evidence-stand-down-order-benghazi |first=David |last=French |publisher=National Review |date=2016-01-15 |accessdate=2017-03-30 |archive-date=2017-03-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170330174706/http://www.nationalreview.com/corner/429855/13-hours-yes-there-evidence-stand-down-order-benghazi |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

参与行动的中情局約聘人员克里斯·“坦托”·帕伦多表示：“我们被告知‘休整’。这些词100%准确。如果事实上有可能影响到某人的仕途？好吧，我很抱歉，的确是<ref>{{cite web|title = New Benghazi movie reignites ‘stand-down’ order debate|url = http://www.politico.com/story/2016/01/benghazi-movie-stand-down-order-debate-217622|website = POLITICO|accessdate = 2016-01-18|archive-date = 2016-01-17|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160117135427/http://www.politico.com/story/2016/01/benghazi-movie-stand-down-order-debate-217622|dead-url = no}}</ref>。”影片刻画的中情局基地主管直接批驳帕伦多的说法，声称“从未有过休整命令......我从未事后猜测队伍将离开<ref>{{cite web|last=Daly|first=Matthew|title=AP FACT CHECK: Benghazi movie misstates some facts|url=http://wtop.com/movies/2016/01/ap-fact-check-benghazi-movie-misstates-some-facts/|publisher=WTOP (Associated Press)|date=2016-01-20|access-date=2016-05-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160415024226/http://wtop.com/movies/2016/01/ap-fact-check-benghazi-movie-misstates-some-facts/|archive-date=2016-04-15|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。”

此外，对空中支援的描绘也颇具争议。众议院军事委员会报告显示空中支援无法使用，或者说来得太晚无法发挥作用<ref name=M.S.R. >{{cite news|author1=M.S.R.|title=Could a Hollywood film about Benghazi damage Clinton?|url=http://www.economist.com/blogs/democracyinamerica/2016/01/outstandown-nonsense-0|date=2016-01-18|accessdate=2016-01-19|work=The Economist|archive-date=2016-01-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160119013733/http://www.economist.com/blogs/democracyinamerica/2016/01/outstandown-nonsense-0|dead-url=no}}</ref>。芬奇则为影片空中支援的描写辩解称，尽管那时不能投放资源，但空中支援本来就动荡不安的利比亚，本身很“荒谬”<ref name="French"/>。2016年7月，共和党主导的众议院班加西特别委员会发布的报告囊括的多份证词，暗示美军可以派出援手，但没收到指示。报告表明国防部没有提供当晚可用军备的许可清单<ref>{{cite web |url=http://benghazi.house.gov/NewInfo |title=Select Committee on Benghazi Releases Proposed Report | Select Committee on Benghazi |publisher=Benghazi.house.gov |date= |accessdate=2016-10-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161013190741/http://benghazi.house.gov/NewInfo |archivedate=2016-10-13 |df= }}</ref>。

美国保守派专栏作家{{le|德莫瑞·默多克|Deroy Murdock}}写道，影片证实其总统[[巴拉克·奥巴马|巴拉克·奥巴马]]和[[美国国务卿|国务卿]][[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]最初在事发数周后谴责[[YouTube|YouTube]]影片《[[穆斯林的无知|穆斯林的无知]]》时撒了谎的个人看法。影片引发全球穆斯林的抗议，奥巴马等人于是公开宣称班加西袭击是示威导致的。默多克注意到，影片描绘的反而是“清楚自己要干什么的精英圣战分子”发动袭击<ref name="murdock">{{cite web |title=13 Hours Confirms Obama's and Hillary Clinton's Lies about Benghazi |url=http://www.nationalreview.com/article/430080/13-hours-movie-benghazi-obama-hillary-clinton |first=Deroy |last=Murdock |work=National Review |date=2016-01-21 |accessdate=2017-03-30 |archive-date=2017-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170308202434/http://www.nationalreview.com/article/430080/13-hours-movie-benghazi-obama-hillary-clinton |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

